  <!--  
    You don't need to include "public" in the href path here. This is because app.use(express.static('./public')) in your server code tells Express to serve files from the "public" folder automatically. That means,
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../stylesheets/indexCSS.css">
    will look for "public/stylesheets/indexCSS.css" by default.

    "../" at the start of the file path just means "go up one folder from the current web address."
    This is needed because the 'stylesheets' folder is not in the same folder as this HTML file.
    So, "../stylesheets/indexCSS.css" tells the browser: look one level higher, then find "stylesheets/indexCSS.css".
    It is about how the web address works, not the folder structure on your computer.
  -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../stylesheets/indexCSS.css">
</head>

